OL,3,GDumfries, Galloway, Lothian & Borders
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FThe morning will begin dry with
OL,6,Fsunny spells and a patchy frost. Cloud
OL,7,Fwill spread northeast during the
OL,8,Fmorning. Outbreaks of rain develop in
OL,9,Fthe afternoon, heaviest and most
OL,10,Fpersistent in the southwest.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FCloudy with some outbreaks of
OL,13,Frain through the evening. Staying
OL,14,Fcloudy overnight with heavier bursts
OL,15,Fof rain developing at times. Strong
OL,16,Fsoutheast winds around the coast.
OL,17,
OL,18,CWednesday:FCloudy as bands of rain
OL,19,Fpush northeast in the morning. Turning
OL,20,Fshowery later, these showers heavy and
OL,21,Fthundery at times.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
